{{Infobox book | italic title = <!--(see above)--> | name = The Cambridge Dictionary of Sociology | image = The Cambridge Dictionary of Sociology.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = | author = [[Bryan S. Turner]] (editor) | audio_read_by = | title_orig = | orig_lang_code = | title_working = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = [[United Kingdom]] | language = English | series = | release_number = | subject = Sociology | genre = | set_in = | published = | publisher = | publisher2 = | pub_date = 2006 | english_pub_date = | media_type = | pages = 686 | awards = | isbn = 9780521540469 | isbn_note = | oclc = 70173369 | dewey = 301 | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = | native_wikisource = | wikisource = | notes = | exclude_cover = | website = [http://www.cambridge.org/features/sociology/turner/ Official] }} '''''The Cambridge Dictionary of Sociology''''' is a [[dictionary]] of [[Sociology|sociological]] terms published by [[Cambridge University Press]] and edited by [[Bryan S. Turner]]. There has only been one edition so far. The Board of Editorial Advisors is made up of: [[Bryan S. Turner]], Ira Cohen, [[Jeff Manza]], Gianfranco Poggi, Beth Schneider, Susan Silbey, and [[Carol Smart]]. In addition there are nearly 100 other contributors.
==References== *{{cite book | last = Turner | first = Bryan | title = The Cambridge dictionary of sociology | publisher = Cambridge University Press | location = Cambridge England New York | year = 2006 | isbn = 9780521540469 }}
